I took a trip to the @hm in @centralworld Bangkok, Thailand and I loved it. The store was super clean, organized, and dope. 

 The store featured a cafe, a home section, and a music studio. The flower shop was my absolute favorite part of the store but unfortunately I didn’t get to make a purchase.  If you visit Bangkok, Thailand, be sure to visit this mall and be ready to spend a few hours there.

Now you know two months is too long to be away from in-feed posting….don’t worry because I am yelling at myself.

•Why does the end/beginning of the year drag me by my edges? I am working on shifting the space that I allow myself to be during this time and ready to get focused 
• Why do I take pictures/videos to post & never post them? Is it because I get in my head too much? 
•Do you want to know what is holding me back? The short answer is ME

Everyday is a new day for us to get it right. So be patient with yourself, do the things that bring you joy, share the things that make you happy, and continue to stay true to who you are. Stress can kill us so we not stressing today. Happy February & enjoy this short clip from Thailand ❤️

The Spring/Summer is when you see a lot of black women wearing a head full of braids. So I decided to stop hiding in my stories (even tho we have great convos in the DMs😂) & I am posting some of my favorite products to use while I have braids.

Easter Sunday in the black household just hits different. As we prepare for tomorrow it just brings me back to these photos as a child. Church has always been a part of our Easter because I grew up with my grandfather as my Pastor. 

I remember preparing for Sunday with my mom getting us new dresses, shoes, socks, stockings, and figuring out how we would wear our hair. I can remember Easter egg hunts and dinner at my grandparents. Just so many moments and times I wish we could get back. Church is also where my first love of style came because I always loved how fly my Sweetmom (grandma) was and the other ladies in the church (fun fact: I am COGIC😉). So while tomorrow makes me happy because I know that HE LIVES, at the same time it makes me emotional because I am reminded of the time we cannot get back❤️ #thekitoyourstyle
When all else fails, I am always going to choose denim on denim #thekitoyourstyle

Playoff Szn in Style: For my Plus-Size Girlies (here is a tip⬇️)

Have you ever went in the Big & Tall section in @burlingtondeals ? I wandered in that section one day and now it is my favorite section to visit first. I recently snagged this @mitchellandness x @sixers oversized shirt for the playoff game and baybeee!!! I could of sized down but I loved that it was truly oversized. Being that I am plus-size & 5’10”, I sometimes have a hard time with getting the actual oversized fit that I want and need. Luckily I have been able to purchase denim jackets, flannels, and denim shirts from this section. Be sure to check it out next time you are in store. #thekitoyourstyle

Adulting can really drag you by the edges some weeks. It feels like time is flying by but moving slow at the same time. You are trying to fit a 1000 things in a day while also carving out time for yourself. Everything is getting expensive, we are losing people we love, working just to pay bills, trying to show up for the people we love, and also trying to do the things that we are passionate about. Some weeks you feel so accomplished and other weeks you feel like you are failing in every area. All we can do is keep waking up and doing what we can. Everyday won’t be perfect but as long as we keep going then we will be good🫶🏾❤️

What do you think is the biggest challenge of showing up for yourself every day? I believe that your mental health plays a major role in how you navigate all aspects of your life, especially when it comes to pushing your limits physically. Some people find it empowering to push through and block out distractions, while others might feel the need to withdraw. We all have those tough days where life drags us by the edges...but can”t stop won’t stop. Shoutout to @_drewrenee_ and @alphasonly.eb for providing the much-needed encouragement during this final stretch on Wednesday night.

Did you catch the sale?

When @greedyinthecity hosts a Happy Hour at @meimeiphilly you better come running. The vibes were vibing, the food was amazing (as always) and the drinks were made for the girls!!! Mei Mei recently introduced two new cocktails to their menu, one is the MEI BAE (made with @bacardi) and the other is the DEP GAI meaning Beautiful Girl in Vietnamese (made with @kikivodka and created by @neisavegetables). They are both worth ordering while you look over the menu, during happy hour, and even once your dinner hits the table.

Grab your girls, book a table, and get out to enjoy yourselves. Stay tuned for more events curated by @thejuicewithjae ❤️
